com.facetec.sdk

Enum FaceTecSessionStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<FaceTecSessionStatus>
      • com.facetec.sdk.FaceTecSessionStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<FaceTecSessionStatus>

    public enum FaceTecSessionStatus
extends java.lang.Enum<FaceTecSessionStatus>
    Represents a description of what happened during a Session. This will be available after a Session
    returns to your application. To get the status of the result object you will call getStatus() which will return an
    enum which gives a short description of what happened during session.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CAMERA_INITIALIZATION_ISSUE
      The Session was cancelled because was unable to start the camera on this device.
      CAMERA_PERMISSION_DENIED
      The camera access is prevented due to the user explicitly denying permission.
      CONTEXT_SWITCH
      The Session was cancelled due to the app being terminated, put to sleep, an OS notification, or the app was placed in the background.
      ENCRYPTION_KEY_INVALID
      The Session was cancelled because the developer-configured encryption key was not valid.
      GRACE_PERIOD_EXCEEDED
      The Session was cancelled because your key needs to be validated again.
      LANDSCAPE_MODE_NOT_ALLOWED
      Session was cancelled because device is in landscape mode.
      The user experience of devices in these orientations is poor and thus portrait is required.
      LOCKED_OUT
      The Session was cancelled because the user was in a locked out state.
      MISSING_GUIDANCE_IMAGES
      The Session was cancelled because not all guidance images were configured.
      NON_PRODUCTION_MODE_KEY_INVALID
      This status will never be returned in a properly configured or production app.
      NON_PRODUCTION_MODE_NETWORK_REQUIRED
      The Session was cancelled because your App is not in production and requires a network connection.
      REVERSE_PORTRAIT_NOT_ALLOWED
      Session was cancelled because device is in reverse portrait mode.
      The user experience of devices in these orientations is poor and thus portrait is required.
      SESSION_COMPLETED_SUCCESSFULLY
      The Session was performed successfully and a FaceScan was generated.
      SESSION_UNSUCCESSFUL
      The Session was not performed successfully and a FaceScan was not generated.
      TIMEOUT
      The Session was cancelled because the user was unable to complete a Session in the default allotted time or the timeout set by the developer.
      UNKNOWN_INTERNAL_ERROR
      The Session was cancelled because of an unknown and unexpected error.
      FaceTec SDK leverages a variety of Android APIs including camera, storage, security, networking, and more.
      This return value is a catch-all for errors experienced during normal usage of these APIs.
      USER_CANCELLED
      The user pressed the cancel button and did not complete the Session.
      USER_CANCELLED_VIA_CLICKABLE_READY_SCREEN_SUBTEXT
      The Session cancelled because user pressed the Get Ready screen subtext message.
      Note: This functionality is not available by default, and must be requested from FaceTec in order to enable.
      USER_CANCELLED_VIA_HARDWARE_BUTTON
      TThe user pressed the cancel button (hardware) and did not complete the Session.
